        <p>German pharmacist, writer, and bryologist. Practiced pharmacy in various parts of Germany until 1843 and then maintained himself chiefly as a freelance writer. Studied at the University of Halle, 1843–6. Assistant editor, <hi rend="italic">Botanische Zeitung</hi>, 1843. Co-founder of the popular journal <hi rend="italic">Die Natur</hi>, 1852.</p></note>
